data.enText: the day of the week after Monday and before Wednesday

data.text: To see how Tuesday is used, look at the examples at Monday .
Tuesday的用法见词条Monday下的示例。

data.enText: Originally translated from the Latin for ‘day of Mars’ dies Marti and named after the Germanic god Tiw .
data.chText: 译自拉丁文dies Marti，原意为day of Mars（战神日），以日耳曼神Tiw（蒂乌）命名。

example.ex: He phoned on Tuesday, just before you came...
example.tran: 他星期二来电话了，就在你来之前。

example.ex: Talks are likely to start next Tuesday…
example.tran: 会谈有可能下周二开始。

example.ex: On Tuesdays and Saturdays the market comes to town.
example.tran: 每逢周二与周六，镇上就会有集市。

value.def: Tuesday is the day after Monday and before Wednesday.

trans: 忏悔日(基督教大斋期的前一天)
超级星期二(美国几个州的初选日)
